<title level="a">LUDVIG HJALMAR LUND</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>Ludvig H. Lund was born in Kristiania April 8, 1870.</p>
   <p>Lund started his career as journalist and writer at an early age. He traveled in continental Europe for several years, and came to Chicago at the age of twenty-one. He worked in various Scandinavian bookstores, such as Skandinaven's, and at John Relling's book store, Milwaukee and Chicago Avenues.</p>
   <p>He was for many years editor of Scandia. Lund was, politically, a Socialist. He belonged to all the major Norwegian societies in Chicago.</p>
